{"id":"4653","name":"DVB Streamer","tagline":"This shortcuts streams a selected tv channel from your STB (E2/Linux-based)","icon":"ios13 c1440408063 g59699","latest":"15058","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>DVB Streamer (STB → iOS)</h2>\n<p>This shortcut is an easy way to watch a chosen tv channel from your STB on your iOS device.</p>\n<p>It works with linux-based <strong>Enigma2</strong> Receivers (DVB-C/S/T2):\n</p><ul>\n<li>Dreambox</li>\n<li>VU+</li>\n<li>Edision</li>\n<li>GigaBlue</li>\n<li>Octagon</li>\n</ul><p></p>\n<p>Upon installation the shortcut asks for the ip address of your receiver as well as the web interface port (default: 80), the streaming port (default: 8001) and optionally username and password (in case you have web authentication enabled).</p>\n<p>The shortcut shows all bouquets from your channel list and you can choose which channel you‘d like to watch. The tv live stream will then be played in <strong>VLC for Mobile</strong>. It‘s possible to change the audio track (if available).</p>\n<p><strong>Preview:</strong></p>\n<p>Screenshot:\n<img alt=\"screenshot\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/m1UzIEz.jpg\"></p><p></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Feb. 26, 2020, 2:24 p.m.</strong></p>"}